      <hedline>
        <hl1>Pack Away Those Lasers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jason S Ganz letter on Aug 10 article on teachers' efforts to combat unneeded technology in schools</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a very concerned 10th grader in Hewlett High School, I am writing to thank you for ''The Modern Student: Batteries Not Included'' (Aug. 10). The article explains how teachers are trying (or not trying) to combat this craze of unneeded technology in the schools. I feel that students should limit what they take to school to calculators, the necessities of school (pens, pencils, books) and maybe a Palm Pilot for organizing life. But cell phones, beepers and CD and MP3 players are a huge disruption in class and should be left at home.</p>
        <p>JASON S. GANZ  Hewlett, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
